<div id="review_942777158" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/942777158" />
    <a title="Alice" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/20730180-alice"><img alt="Alice" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1419249812p2/20730180.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/942777158?book_show_action=true">May 20, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Alice" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Alice" href="/user/show/20730180-alice">Alice</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780615718255" href="/book/show/22098327-life-of-love">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/20730180-alice?shelf=giveaway">giveaway</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer942777158" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5733885689059834199">I really want to thank the author - Santonu Dhar - for giving me a free ebook copy of this novel in exchange of an honest review. <br/>It was such an honor, seriously. <br/><br/>First things first: English is not my first language, so feel free to correct me if I make any mistake along the way. <br/><br/>I think the incipit is very strong, at least to me. <br/>The moment John sees Sarah for the very first time reminds me of my first love and the summer I met him. <br/>It was love at first sight on my side. <br/>To him? Not so much. <br/>Th</span>
  <span id="freeText5733885689059834199" style="display:none">I really want to thank the author - Santonu Dhar - for giving me a free ebook copy of this novel in exchange of an honest review. <br />It was such an honor, seriously. <br /><br />First things first: English is not my first language, so feel free to correct me if I make any mistake along the way. <br /><br />I think the incipit is very strong, at least to me. <br />The moment John sees Sarah for the very first time reminds me of my first love and the summer I met him. <br />It was love at first sight on my side. <br />To him? Not so much. <br />The point is that John in the first chapter reminded me so much of myself several years ago and I felt a connection with him for most part of the novel. <br /><br />The story is heavily focused on John and Sarah and their love, relatives and friends and colleagues only make a sporadic appearence here and there. <br />Anyway, there's a character who somehow is relevant too: William. <br /><br />I felt so sad for William.<br />Just like him, I stayed attached to someone even when I knew better that I had to move on with my life but it's a thing easier said than done. <br />I wasn't ready to let go, I didn't <i>want</i> to let go. <br />The only difference between William and I is that I had lost every contact with the object of my affection in the years, unlike him and Sarah. <br /><br />I liked the second half of the novel better than the first. <br />I don't know, things sometimes appeared a little too much rushed to me, but I get it: when you fall in love, there's nothing or anyone else on your mind for a little while. <br />But nonetheless, I really liked John and Sarah's love: sweet, tender and very much "like the first time" even when both of them had past relationships above their shoulders. <br />It was an "all or nothing" kind of love. <br />Yet, even if tragedy strikes towards the end, I liked that part the best. <br />There's something captivating within those words, within the strength you must have to go on with your life and to find the silver lining among the sadness. <br />And Sarah found that, in the end. <br /><br />Like I said, English isn't my first language but this novel was so easy to read and the writing is very smooth throughout the chapters. <br />Great job! </span>
  <a data-text-id="5733885689059834199" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


