<div id="review_794552639" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/794552639" />
    <a title="Book&#39;d Hitu" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5610463-book-d-hitu"><img alt="Book&#39;d Hitu" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1326779417p2/5610463.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/794552639?book_show_action=true">Dec 19, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Book&#39;d Hitu" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Book&#39;d Hitu" href="/user/show/5610463-book-d-hitu">Book&#39;d Hitu</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Everyone</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5610463-book-d-hitu?shelf=review-copy">review-copy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer794552639" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13200387829927495224">I would like to thank the Author Santonu Dhar for providing the review copy in exchange of an honest review.<br/><br/>Life of Love is a cute and sweet love story of a perfect couple Sarah and John. A very simple story line yet the way author has narrated it, will hold the attention of reader till the end.<br/><br/>As soon the Sarah and John fall in love with each other and the story progresses further, I got so attached to both of them that I even thought that, oh god, I know that this is a fiction but don&apos;t let th</span>
  <span id="freeText13200387829927495224" style="display:none">I would like to thank the Author Santonu Dhar for providing the review copy in exchange of an honest review.<br /><br />Life of Love is a cute and sweet love story of a perfect couple Sarah and John. A very simple story line yet the way author has narrated it, will hold the attention of reader till the end.<br /><br />As soon the Sarah and John fall in love with each other and the story progresses further, I got so attached to both of them that I even thought that, oh god, I know that this is a fiction but don't let these two get into any trouble. They were so sweet and perfect to each other. But at the end, a tragedy strikes on both of them and their life turned out to be a roller coaster ride from then.<br /><br />I must say, author has a wonderful command over his words and the prose. I would recommend this book to everyone who loves to read a sweet and simple romance. This is a light and cozy read. Full of emotions and dramatic situations that the readers will love to experience.<br /><br />Four Stars to the story and the narration. Three Stars to the editing as I found a few flaws with the grammar. Best wishes to the author for his next work. I would definitely love to read more of his books in future.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="13200387829927495224" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


