  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/833590912" />
    <a title="Ana" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/14593112-ana"><img alt="Ana" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1396411936p2/14593112.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/833590912?book_show_action=true">Jan 24, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ana" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ana" href="/user/show/14593112-ana">Ana</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/14593112-ana?shelf=read-4-review">read-4-review</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer833590912" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13186041597334750342">I&apos;d like to thank Mr. Santonu Kumar Dhar, for letting me have an ebook copy, in exchange of my honest review, I&apos;m really honored!<br/><br/>If you&apos;re looking for romance, adventure and an easy, but page-turner book... <br/>CONGRATULATIONS! This is your book for sure! <br/><br/>It was a lovely story: perfect for those hopeless romantic kind of people (like me).<br/>Though I have to say, John didn&apos;t really reached my expectations (I felt his character quite flat), he was obviously madly in love with Sarah, who&apos;s feelings for hi</span>
  <span id="freeText13186041597334750342" style="display:none">I'd like to thank Mr. Santonu Kumar Dhar, for letting me have an ebook copy, in exchange of my honest review, I'm really honored!<br /><br />If you're looking for romance, adventure and an easy, but page-turner book... <br />CONGRATULATIONS! This is your book for sure! <br /><br />It was a lovely story: perfect for those hopeless romantic kind of people (like me).<br />Though I have to say, John didn't really reached my expectations (I felt his character quite flat), he was obviously madly in love with Sarah, who's feelings for him were all over the book, they really complemented each other, I have to admit that, and the fact that they both seemed so sure they were soul-mates, brought tears of happiness and sadness at the same time to my eyes, I have so many thoughts in my mind about this, so many bittersweet feelings.. OMG! I'm dying to read the other two books!<br />And last but not least, I have to highlight how perfectly written is this book! Plus it's totally unpredictable in my opinion.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13186041597334750342" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
